title: Opinion: Israel will remain Netanyahu's even if he is no longer prime minister
description: On Sunday night, Naftali Bennett, the right-wing politician who may become Israel's new prime minister in a week, finally broke cover and lambasted his old boss and mentor Benjamin Netanyahu for trying to lead the state of Israel to his own "personal Masada" -- a reference to the Jewish zealots who committed mass suicide rather than become Roman slaves in the first century A.D.

title: Tybee Island lightning strike kills a 15-year-old swimmer
description: A 15-year-old girl died Saturday after she was struck by lightning while swimming off the coast of Georgia, according to the Tybee Island Police Department.

title: Christian Eriksen suffered cardiac arrest and 'was gone' before resuscitation, doctor says
As G7 wraps up, Biden meets the Queen
New Zealand houseplant sells for $19,200 in online bidding war
description: A houseplant with just nine leaves has sold for a record-breaking $19,297 on a New Zealand auction site.

title: Pelosi says House leadership 'did not rebuke' Omar over comments about US, Israel, Hamas and Taliban
description: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Sunday said House leadership "did not rebuke" Democratic Rep. Ilhan Omar last week, after criticism from the left that the caucus was unfairly targeting Omar and mischaracterizing her comments about the US, Israel, Hamas and the Taliban.

title: Analysis: Netanyahu's reign is over for now. He leaves behind a wealthier, more divided Israel and a stalled peace process
description: He's been dubbed King Bibi, the magician, the great survivor, and has held records as both the youngest and longest-serving prime minister of Israel.

title: Israel's new prime minister is sworn in, ending Netanyahu's 12-year grip on power
Benjamin Netanyahu's life in pictures
description: Benjamin Netanyahu, the longest-serving Israeli prime minister in history, might soon find himself out of power.

title: Fareed Zakaria: This is what went wrong for Netanyahu
description: CNN's Fareed Zakaria discusses the impact Benjamin Netanyahu has had on Israel as the country's longest serving prime minister and says legal troubles helped turn many Israelis against him.

title: The pandemic could be Indian leader Modi's undoing. But millions won't ditch him just yet.
Pelosi says Trump DOJ's targeting of enemies 'goes even beyond Nixon'
description: The Trump-era Justice Department's decision to secretly seize data of Democrats on the House Intelligence Committee went even beyond the nefarious actions of former President Richard Nixon, House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said Sunday.

title: Russia willing to extradite cyber criminals to US on reciprocal basis
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin has said his nation is prepared to extradite cyber criminals to the United States on a reciprocal basis, Russia's state-run TASS news agency reported Sunday.

title: DNA leads to surprising discovery of two Viking family members
description: The National Museum of Denmark will display two Viking skeletons, found to be related, that were discovered in different countries. The remains have given researchers a glimpse into Viking life in its heyday.

title: Biden rarely has nice things to say about Putin
description: In 2011, then-Vice President Joe Biden and Russian Prime Minister Vladimir Putin hoped for cooperation between their two countries. A decade later their relationship has deteriorated.

title: Spare ticket for spaceflight with Jeff Bezos auctioned for $28 million
description: What would you pay to take a jolting, 11-minute trip into suborbital space alongside Jeff Bezos? According to bidders in an auction that wrapped up Saturday, it's worth $28 million.

title: Airplane discovered at the bottom of a California lake could be from 1965 crash
description: Workers testing underwater surveying equipment say they found the wreckage of a small airplane deep underwater in California's Folsom Lake -— and they may have solved a 56-year-old aviation mystery.

title: Rescues underway after huge gas explosion in central Chinese city
Wife of detained Nicaraguan activist says regime 'willing to kill'
description: She says she feels angry and desperate, but the way she speaks and what she says make it clear that she refuses to be afraid. Berta Valle is the wife of Félix Maradiaga Blandón, one of at least seven opposition leaders who have been detained in Nicaragua so far this month.

title: Scientists say 90% of the world's open-ocean sharks died off in mystery extinction event 19 million years ago
Former deputy attorney general said he was not aware of subpoena for lawmakers' data, source says
description: Ex-top Trump Justice Department official Rod Rosenstein has told people in recent days he was not aware of a subpoena that targeted the data of Democratic members of Congress while he was deputy attorney general, a source familiar with Rosenstein told CNN on Saturday.

title: Twitter's future in doubt as company under siege in countries critical for growth
